Recommended tools and libraries:

autoconf 2.52g
automake 1.5
libtool 1.4.2
gcc 3.0.3
gmp 4.0.1      (configure with --enable-cxx and using -fexceptions) (1)
cln 1.1.4      (ignore the errors given by `make install') (2)
fi_lib++ 2.0   (follow the instructions) (3)
ntl 5.2        (4)
ginac          (use our CVS version and forget about religion) (5)

Just for the web-based demos:

cgicc 3.2      (see http://www.gnu.org/software/cgicc/cgicc.html
                and configure with --enable-namespaces)
 

(1)
Your configure command should be something like

CPPFLAGS=-fexceptions my/path/to/gmp-4.0.1/configure --prefix=/usr/local --enable-cxx

(2)
Build cln out of the source tree, then ignore the error about
a missing cln.m4 when you do `make install'.
Note that if you had already installed cln before (from inside
the source tree), you should remove by hand the previously
installed configuration file <prefix>/share/aclocal/cln.m4

(3)
mkdir filib++
cd filib++
cvs -d cvs.cs.unipr.it:/cvs/filib++ checkout interval
cd interval
ln -s makefiles/Makefile.gcc Makefile
make libs
(it will complain because some `lib' directory is missing: create it by hand)
make libs
su
<root password>
make install

(4)
tar zxf ntl-5.2.tar.gz
cd ntl-5.2/src
./configure NTL_GMP_LIP=on NTL_STD_CXX=on GMP_PREFIX=/usr/local
make
make check
su
<root password>
make install

(5)
cvs -d cvs.cs.unipr.it:/cvs/GiNaC checkout GiNaC
touch Makefile.in aclocal.m4 configure
mkdir /tmp/objdir
cd /tmp/objdir
~/GiNaC/configure --prefix=/usr/local
make
su
<root password>
make install
